The patient presents with a tingling sensation on the lateral side of his right forearm after lifting heavy weights at the gym. The loss of sensation on the lateral side of the forearm, with intact sensation over the thumb, suggests an injury to the radial nerve. The radial nerve is responsible for sensation on the lateral side of the forearm and is also involved in the motor function of wrist extension.

Further examination of this patient is most likely to show weakness of wrist extension, which is the action primarily controlled by the radial nerve. Wrist extension is the movement of the wrist upwards, towards the back of the hand.

